HEADWORD: Ischiadic
<hw>Is`chi*ad"ic</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧s`k⟦icr⟧*⟦acr⟧d"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>ischiadicus</ets>, Gr.
<grk>'ischiadoko`s</grk>, fr. <grk>'ischi`on</grk> the hip joint, hip or
loin. Cf. <er>Sciatic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Ischial.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Ischiadic passion</b></col> <it>or</it>
<col><b>Ischiadic disease</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Med.)</fld>, <cd>a
rheumatic or neuralgic affection of some part about the hip joint; --
called also <altname>sciatica</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ischial</ent>⟦br⟧
